items.name: static let `default`: CAMediaTimingFunctionName
items.desc: The system default timing function. Use this function to ensure that the timing of your animations matches that of most system animations.

items.name: static let easeIn: CAMediaTimingFunctionName
items.desc: Ease-in pacing, which causes an animation to begin slowly and then speed up as it progresses.

items.name: static let easeInEaseOut: CAMediaTimingFunctionName
items.desc: Ease-in-ease-out pacing, which causes an animation to begin slowly, accelerate through the middle of its duration, and then slow again before completing.

items.name: static let easeOut: CAMediaTimingFunctionName
items.desc: Ease-out pacing, which causes an animation to begin quickly and then slow as it progresses.

items.name: static let linear: CAMediaTimingFunctionName
items.desc: Linear pacing, which causes an animation to occur evenly over its duration.
